"n.慷慨援助；施舍 【英】 n. 慷慨援助(generous giving)；施舍(a gift or gifts given) 【考】 反义词：parsimony( 吝啬) 【记】 large(大)+sse→大方 n. 慷慨援助; 施舍 【记】large大－大方施舍 【反】parsimony(n 过度节俭; 吝啬); penury(n 贫困; 贫穷) 【记】large 大方 largesse (n.)  also largess, ""willingness to give or spend freely; munificence,"" c.1200, from Old French largesse ""a bounty, munificence,"" from Vulgar Latin *largitia ""abundance,"" from Latin largus ""abundant"" (see large). In medieval theology, ""the virtue whose opposite is avarice, and whose excess is prodigality"" [""Middle English Dictionary""]. The Old French suffix -esse is from Latin -itia, added to adjectives to form nouns of quality (compare duress, riches)."
